revision.text:
{{Orphan|date=December 2016}}
Academician '''Aliashraf Abdulhuseyn oghlu Alizade''' (1911&ndash;1985) was an [[Azerbaijan]]i [[geologist]]. He was a full member and one of the founders of the [[Azerbaijan National Academy of Sciences]] (1945),<ref name="ANASbio">{{cite web|url=http://science.gov.az/forms/osnovateli-nana/2628 |title=Əlizadə Ələşrəf Əbdülhüseyn oğlu |language=Azerbaijani |trans-title=Alizadeh Alashraf son Abdulhuseyn |work=The founders of the National Academy of Sciences |publisher=[[Azerbaijan National Academy of Sciences]] |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161228235837/http://science.gov.az/forms/osnovateli-nana/2628 |archivedate=28 December 2016 |accessdate=28 December 2016 }}</ref> and an Honorary Oilman of the USSR (1971). He was also a State Award laureate for the discovery and exploitation of new oil fields (1943) and for the preparation of the small electric perforator (1946).

