{{Expand Dutch|Westerpark|date=September 2016}} {{Infobox park | name = Westerpark | photo = Westerpark zomer.jpg | photo_width = 200px | photo_caption = | type = [[Urban park]] | location = [[Westerpark (stadsdeel)|Westerpark]], [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]] | coords = | area = | created = | operator = | visitation_num = | status = Open all year }}
The "Westerpark" ([[English language|English]]: "Western Park") is a [[public park|public]] [[urban park]] in [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]]. The former borough (''[[stadsdeel]]'') of [[Westerpark (former borough)|Westerpark]] is named after the park, as is the current [[Westerpark (neighborhood)|neighborhood]]. In 2012 opposite the park, two trains were involved in a [[2012 Sloterdijk train collision|head-on collision]]. The verdant space of the former [[Westergasfabriek]] [[gasworks]] along Haarlemmerweg has become a place for cultural avant-garde businesses and events.
'''Westergasfabriek''' To the west of the park lies a historical building known as Westergasfabriek. The building was built in 1883. The historic building has been renovated and are now used by creative and cultural entrepreneurs.
